<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - CYLINDER SLEEVE
        REMOVAL - CONNECTING ROD, PISTON AND RING DISASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CONNECTING ROD, PISTON AND RING DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using pliers, remove the two piston retaining rings. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150611">6.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4150610" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11966" filename="../figcg1/CG11966.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.10. Remove Cylinder Sleeve.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150611" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11559" filename="../figcg1/CG11559.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.11. Remove Piston Pin Retaining Rings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the piston pin from its bore, by hand. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_108.xml" xrefid="ef4150612">6.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                . Then separate the connecting rod from the piston.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a piston ring expander tool to remove the piston rings. remove the top ring first, then
                the second ring and the oil control ring. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_108.xml" xrefid="ef4150613">6.13</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tag or mark the components with the cylinder number from which they were removed, so they
                may be reinstalled in their respective cylinders once inspected.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
